headlines.description: Jalen Brunson scored 31 points despite leaving the game briefly with a left ankle injury, Donte DiVincenzo added 23 and top-ranked Villanova avoided another upset in Milwaukee with an 85-82 win Sunday over Marquette.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson, No. 1 Villanova hold on, beat Marquette 85-82

headlines.description: Isaac Haas matched his career high with 26 points, Vincent Edwards added 19 and No. 3 Purdue held off Indiana 74-67 on Sunday for its school-record 17th consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 3 Purdue holds off Indiana for record 17th straight win

video.headline: Purdue improves to 10-0 in Big Ten play

headlines.description: Joshua Langford scored 19 points and led a second-half surge that carried No. 6 Michigan State past fading Maryland 74-68 Sunday, giving Spartans coach Tom Izzo his seventh straight 20-win season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Langford scores 19 as No. 6 Michigan St beats Maryland 74-68

headlines.description: Austin Reaves hit seven 3-pointers in the first half and scored all of his career-high 23 points before halftime to lead No. 17 Wichita State over Tulsa 90-71 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 17 Wichita State pulls away to beat Tulsa 90-71

headlines.description: Gabe DeVoe scored a career-high 25 points, Marcquise Reed hit a decisive layup in the closing seconds and No. 18 Clemson held off Georgia Tech 72-70 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeVoe, Reed help No. 18 Clemson hold off Georgia Tech

headlines.description: Matt Mobley made five 3-pointers and scored 24 points, 16 in the second half, and St. Bonaventure defeated George Washington 70-52 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mobley scores 24 points in Bonnies' 70-52 win over Colonials

headlines.description: Stephen Brown scored 21 points and Bucknell avenged its last loss and opened a two-game lead atop the Patriot League with a 91-79 win over Boston University on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucknell whips BU 91-79, takes control of Patriot League

headlines.description: Jerome Desrosiers scored 14 points, Devin Cannady 12 and Myles Stephens 10 -- all but eight of those 36 points coming in the first half when the game was decided -- and Princeton rolled past Rowan 86-50 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Princeton rolls to big halftime lead, cruises to 86-50 win

headlines.description: Carson Williams scored 13 points, Drew McDonald added 12 and Northern Kentucky cruised to a 72-44 win over Detroit Mercy on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northern Kentucky rolls to 72-44 win over Detroit Mercy

headlines.description: Jimmy Whitt scored a career-high 20 points, Jahmal McMurray made four 3-pointers and also scored 20 and SMU beat East Carolina 86-61 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Whitt, McMurray lead SMU past ECU 86-61

headlines.description: Nate Kennell hit 7 of 9 3-point attempts and scored a career-high 25 points to lead Bradley over Indiana State 81-73 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kennell makes 7 3s in Bradley's first MVC road win, 81-73

headlines.description: Grant Golden scored 24 points on 11-of-15 shooting, Nick Sherod had 10 points, 14 boards and four assists, and Richmond beat Davidson 66-63 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Richmond tops Davidson, wins 4th straight in the series

headlines.description: Blake Francis scored 21 points with five 3-pointers, JoJo Cooper scored 17 with nine assists and Wagner beat Robert Morris 77-64 on Sunday to take sole possession of first place in the Northeast Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner sits atop NEC after 77-64 win over Robert Morris

headlines.description: Jamaal King scored 21 points and fed Scott Meredith for a 3-pointer with three seconds left to give St. Francis (PA) a 72-71 win over Sacred Heart on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: St. Francis (PA) outlast Sacred Heart with 72-71 win

headlines.description: Freshman Loudon Love had a double-double in the first half and finished with 18 points and a season-high tying 17 rebounds to lead Wright State by Oakland 64-51 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: 1st place Wright State beats Oakland 64-51

headlines.description: Corey Davis Jr. scored 17 points and made 4 of 5 3-pointers and Fabian White Jr. had a double-double and Houston beat struggling South Florida 63-40 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Houston downs cold-shooting USF 63-40 behind Davis and White

headlines.description: Jonah Mathews and Elijah Stewart each scored 16 points to lead USC to a 77-59 victory over Cal on Sunday at USC.
headlines.shortLinkText: USC cruises to sixth straight win over struggling Cal

headlines.description: Angel Delgado grabbed 19 rebounds to become the all-time Big East leader in conference games, Myles Powell scored 21 points and Seton Hall defeated DePaul 86-70 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Delgado sets Big East record in Seton Hall's 86-70 victory

video.headline: Rodriguez knocks down 3 for Seton Hall

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Rodriguez knocks down 3 for Seton Hall) 2018/01/28 esheet

headlines.description: Clayton Custer scored a season-high 21 points on 9-of-12 shooting and Missouri Valley Conference leader Loyola-Chicago beat Northern Iowa 70-47 on Sunday for its seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: MVC leader Loyola-Chicago wins 7th straight, tops UNI 70-47

headlines.description: Shizz Alston Jr. scored 18 points, Quinton Rose had 17 and Temple rolled to an 85-57 win over UConn on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alston Jr., Rose lead Temple to 85-57 rout of slumping UConn

video.headline: Aflakpui wins in the post to extend the Owls' lead

headlines.description: Mattise Thybulle scored 18 points and freshman Jaylen Nowell added 14 points and a team-high nine rebounds to pace Washington to an 80-62 victory over Washington State in a Pac-12 Conference game on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thybulle, Nowell pace Washington past Washington State 80-62

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.
nowFeed.story: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
